# GEMINI.md — Gemini CLI adapter for Solon SFS

This project uses Solon SFS.

Before planning or editing, read:

- `SFS.md`
- `.sfs-local/VERSION`
- `.sfs-local/divisions.yaml`
- recent files under `.sfs-local/sprints/`
- recent files under `.sfs-local/decisions/`

Gemini CLI does not need a native `/sfs` slash command. Treat these user requests as SFS commands:

- `sfs status`, `/sfs status`: summarize current SFS state and next action.
- `sfs start <goal>`, `/sfs start <goal>`: create or continue the current sprint; use `--id <sprint-id>` only when a custom id is required.
- `sfs plan`: write or update the current sprint `plan.md`.
- `sfs review`: write or update the current sprint `review.md`.
- `sfs decision <decision>`: record a short ADR under `.sfs-local/decisions/`.
- `sfs retro`: write or update the current sprint `retro.md`.

Preserve user work. Ask only when a decision changes behavior or could discard work.
